                  <handDesc>
                     
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Mediocre but careful</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black (reddish brown); red (vivid red)</seg>
                        <date>Second half of the 19th century-first half of the 20th century</date>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; names of the donors; incipit of Text
                           I; incipit of the prayers to be read; directives to the ministers; word
                           yǝbärǝkǝwwo (fols. 3v-4v) and its two first letters; words säbbuḥni
                           (fols. 3v-4r), la-ʾǝgziʾabǝḥer (fols. 4v-5r) and their abbreviations;
                           sentence nǝsebbǝḥakä ʾǝgziʾo and its abbreviation (fols. 24v-29r); words
                           yǝtʾakkʷät, its two first letters and its abbreviation (fols. 31r-31v);
                           elements of the punctuation signs; Ethiopic numerals.</seg>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="e1">
                           <desc type="findingAid">- Daily readings are indicated by the names of the
                              days of the week written in the upper margin: ዘሰኑይ: <locus target="#1r">fol. 1r</locus>. ዘሠሉስ: <locus target="#5v">fol.
                                 5v</locus>. ዘረቡዕ: <locus target="#9r">fol. 9r</locus>. ዘዓርብ: <locus target="#21r">fol. 21r</locus>. ዘቀዳም: <locus target="#29r">fol.
                                 29r</locus>. ዘእሁድ: <locus target="#34">fol.
                           34</locus>.</desc>
                        </item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
